ts for the child to exit and collect all remaining\r\n    /// output on the stdout/stderr handles, returning an `Output`\r\n    /// instance.\r\n    ///\r\n    /// The stdin handle to the child process, if any, will be closed\r\n    /// before waiting.\r\n```\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n        drop(self.stdin.take());\r\n        match (self.stdout.take(), self.stderr.take()) {\r\n            // ...\r\n            (Some(out), Some(err)) => {\r\n                let res = read2(out.inner, &mut stdout, err.inner, &mut stderr);\r\n                res.unwrap();\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        let status = self.wait()?;\r\n```\r\n\r\nRight now it closes stdin, collects output and then starts to wait for the process to finish, ignoring its output. This doesn't look like intended behavior.", "closed_by": {"login": "pzmarzly", "id": 8074163, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjgwNzQxNjM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8074163?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly", "html_url": "https://github.com/pzmarzly", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pzmarzly/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/53402/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/r